                    <p style="text-align:justify;">Fundação Gino Favaro is a foundation headed by the President <span class="fst-italic">Director Mr. Gino Ernesto Favaro</span>, a son of an Italian
                      /Australian immigrant from Darwin, Australia who started to live in Timor-Leste (then Portuguese Timor) in the year 1970. Mr. Gino Favaro has witnessed the struggles of Timor-Leste up to and beyond the independence of the Nation. Mr. Gino Favaro accepted the Very Rare Opportunity with Immense Honor of donating to the people of Timor-Leste a special gift, The very first Constitutional National Ceremonial flag of the tiny Nation. Thus, has enhanced the reputation of his name in the Nation of Timor-Leste.</p>
                    <p style="text-align:justify;">Now, let us chat about the Foundation and its essence to the people of Timor-Leste.
                      The Foundation has three main objectives: <br><span class="fst-italic">(The Following are from the words of Mr. Gino Favaro)</span></p>
                      <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
                        <img src="<?php echo base_url(); ?>/image/blog_imgs/1.png" alt="" style="width:500px; height: 350px;">
                      </div>
                    <figure>
                        <blockquote class="blockquote">
                            <p class="mb-0" style="text-align:justify;">The Fundação Gino Favaro first objective is to promote and develop and engage in the tourism and hospitality industry, including religious tourism, cultural tourism, historical tourism, and other special tourism aspects.
                              To engage in the Hospitality & Tourism Industry in providing Quality Hotels and International Standard Tourism Facilities all around Timor-Leste.</p>
                        </blockquote>
                    </figure>
                    <p style="text-align:justify;">There are very few hotels around the country side and not many that are categorized as Premium Hotels accept in
                      the Capital of Dili. If the Timor-Leste Government allows it to develop the country in accordance with the Timor-Leste National Tourism Policy “GROWING TOURISM TO 2030, Enhancing a National Identity this world be a majot benefit for the Fundação Gino Favaro.</p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">The Fundação wants to build and operate fully functional Quality Hotels with Shopping Facilities
                      throughout the country. To develop and manage to International Standards, Tourism locations across the
                      country as many of these locations have no roads or facilities at these spots, travelers have mentioned that they would like to
                      explore these special locations but when they have to walk between 3 to 4 km by foot after parking the car to get to this location their desire dwindles a bit.</p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">This is where the Fundação wishes to seek donor funding to develop these special locations so that they are made available for all to see and explore and use. These hotels with shopping centers and international standard, tourism facilities will be available to local and international travelers’ and will be specially built as practical training facilities for Timorese Students, so as to enhance the professional level of students wanting to enter the industry. It is intended that these student training facilities will have suitable student accommodation, other student facilities, food canteens, so that the students can Learn, Work and Rest in the knowledge that they are being respected as potentially important people of the industry. It is the intentions of the Fundação Gino Favaro to fully co-operate with the Ministry of Education and the Ministry of Tourism and Trade and other relevant Ministries of the Government of Timor-Leste, in order to achieve these goals.
                    </p>

