                    </div>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">The objectives of Fundação Gino Favaro we have talked about so far seem very essential to the improvement of the quality of life to all those people that will receive a change in life due to the installation of natural gas and fresh water to each house and further appreciate that students will also enjoy the benefits of the specialized practical training facilities that will be on offer and I believe that the students that pass the written tests and practical exams of these programs are headed for a great future, possibly a great chance of enjoying long term employment with the Fundação’s many new hotels or tourism locations  or even working with the natural gas and fresh water network systems, not to mention all of the other projects we have not discussed as yet. We can see from these desires of the Fundação the future students could have a quality job in the industry and feel confident and secure in themselves that they are professional in their chosen field. And that they thoroughly understand their new responsibilities and commitments and are able to carry out their new job with expertise.
                    </p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">The Fundação visualizes how much material benefit and economic benefits of each construction site of a new hotel and each construction site of a new developing tourism location will bring to each and every town or village of the country side with the added benefit of natural gas and fresh water to each house. Then of course those permanent jobs that will be created at each location. The permanent jobs shall bring lasting economic benefits to the many families in each location. The operation of each hotel shall itself bring economic benefits to the local farmers as the hotels will require fresh produce of all descriptions every day. The shopping centers attached to each hotel, I presume, will be specially designed assisting the locals to be able to display and sell their local artifacts and home sewing and indigenous crafts and souvenirs to the shoppers. This will further provide an opportunity for the Ladies of the community to be creative and thus enjoy the economic benefits of these locations.
                    </p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">On the other hand, the classrooms attached to each Practical Training Facility can be used for the upskilling of older members of the communities. Upskilling the older members of the communities allows them to have some time out of the house and allows them to further develop skills of their interests that they may not have been able to do so at any other time of their life. Let’s teach the older members of the communities to use the Internet what abuzz that would be for them since some of them don’t even have a phone. They may not know what the other side of the world looks like, but these classrooms at each Training Facility at each hotel could have a huge positive impact for each community as it offers an opportunity that is not currently available. Lastly, the Fundação understands that the development of each project will be undertaken by as many locals as possible particularly those from the country towns and villages, this will bring economic relief to those smaller towns and villages that would not normally be exposed to such opportunities.
                    </p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fst-italic">(Here ends Mr. Favaro’s words.)</span></p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">These three objectives are just the starting plans of the foundation. But I believe many different successful things could still appear in the near future if enough number of people could hear and listen to the hopes of the Fundação Gino Favaro to the people of Timor-Leste. If anyone is reading this now, now is the time to lend your hands to the people of Timor-Leste. Help them to build a better future for their small Nation. Help them to show what they are capable of.</p>

                    <p style="text-align:justify;">In the next series of this article, we will discuss thoroughly the aims of the Foundation, specifically the Foundation’s plan of the Nation’s religious sites and a brief history of the founders. But for now, I will leave you with a poetry by Mr. Gino Favaro to the Nation of Timor-Leste entitled, “Timor-Leste.”</p>

